      - __init__(x, y): Initialize the player.
      - update(keys): Move horizontally based on key presses and confine within screen bounds.
      - shoot(now_ms): Create a Bullet if cooldown allows; returns Bullet or None.
  - Bullet(pygame.sprite.Sprite)
    - Purpose: Represents a projectile shot by the player.
    - Methods:
      - __init__(x, y, dy): Initialize bullet with vertical velocity dy.
      - update(): Move bullet and kill it when off-screen.
  - Alien(pygame.sprite.Sprite)
    - Purpose: Represents a single alien.
    - Methods:
      - __init__(x, y): Initialize the alien.
      - update(): Aliens are moved by the fleet manager; basic placeholder to match sprite API.

- game.py
  - AlienFleet
    - Purpose: Manage collective movement of the alien formation (horizontal motion, edge detection, downward drops, speed-up).
    - Methods:
      - __init__(aliens_group): Initialize with aliens sprite group.
      - reset_speed(): Reset fleet speed and direction.
      - update(): Move aliens horizontally, drop on edge hit, reverse direction, speed up; track lowest Y.
      - reached_bottom(player_top): Check if any alien has reached or passed the player's top (bottom line).
      - bounds(): Return current min_x and max_x bounds of the fleet.
  - Game
    - Purpose: Main game controller. Handles states, input, updates, collisions, scoring, lives, and rendering.
    - Methods:
      - __init__(): Initialize pygame, screen, groups, fonts, and state.
      - new_game(): Reset to a fresh game with player and initial alien grid.
      - spawn_aliens(rows, cols): Create a formation of aliens.
      - handle_events(): Process input and state transitions.
      - update(): Update entities and game logic based on current state.
      - resolve_collisions(): Handle bullet-alien and alien-player collisions.
      - draw(): Render current frame (background, sprites, UI, and screen overlays for start/victory/game over).
      - lose_life(): Decrement lives and set temporary invulnerability for the player; end game if no lives left.
      - run(): Main loop.

- main.py
  - Purpose: Application entry point; creates Game and runs it.

